<subSubSection id="8A1B7AD44A2EC6683AB0E7312C95A616" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="68DFFE380A7E26AC1A4073632EECD175" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3045142C506F9327B31D19A87DF8CC" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A1F9BAC4B43CE68DE8DCAE761772E2A1" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Asplenium salignum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salignum">
<emphasis id="01ED12CBD6270382D41D09152F35F8D8" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Asplenium salignum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its short creeping rhizome, tuft of simple or once pinnate fronds dentate with rounded marginal teeth but 
<taxonomicName id="53E9E9F63D35C6EA95E572B84C3E9061" class="Poylpodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. merapohense" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" phylum="Polypodiophyta" rank="species" species="merapohense">
<emphasis id="EFCE5494488E72EEC1F6BC33DE4EED27" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">A. merapohense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct in its shorter, much narrower pinnae 3.4-7.1 
<normalizedToken id="96401344DBBB99786C3F4B62FA32F767" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.3(-0.45) cm (vs. 6-27 
<normalizedToken id="28F1087D7ECC6DBB378F9F8B555F8D9B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.9-3.7 cm) and shorter sori, which are 2-6 mm long and lie parallel to the midrib (vs. sori 4-13 mm long angled at 45° to the midrib).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
